Movie: Mission: Impossible – Dead Reckoning Part One

Review: I crieddddd, so fun, funny, and sweet. just enough darkness to feel real without taking away from the Sunny outlook. Lots of long takes with great staging of multiple characters just hanging out and a lot of fun camera movements. Also fun musical scenes

Movie: Puss in Boots: The Last Wish

Review: The dialogue is really bad in this but it’s an amazing escape, I was so there. It didn’t need to be 3 hours tho. Gorgeous details except my eyes started to glaze over the 4th time something was happening again.

Loved this. The dread starts immediately without distracting from character development.Slight spoilers below, nothing very specific. But as everyone else is saying, it’s really fun to go into this movie cold. I love basements. There could be literally anything in there and it’s such a fun device for the writer to do whatever they want to the plot. I’m thinking about Parasite (!!!!) & Don’t Breathe and I’m sure there’s a great supercut somewhere of basement reveals in movies.And the basement…

Soooo brutal. The movie slow builds to some really intense action with no soundtrack. The weapons are terrifying, you can feel and hear each strike in crisp detail. Unexpectedly strong character details. Hollywood tends to apply a level of cleanliness & shimmer to genre films that doesn’t feel present here.
